The President also sees it as a way to regain popular and democratic legitimacy as the country is in a state of protest.
Mohammed Morsi seems convinced that the Egyptians will vote in favour, as he asserted in an interview with the American weekly Time.
The use of a rushed vote is an ultimatum to the Egyptian people: "Either you vote for my text or I hold full power", and it is supposed to end after the Constitution is adopted.
It was in a strange atmosphere that 85 members of this constituent assembly, overwhelmingly Islamists, voted yesterday on the text.
Most of the Liberals were out of the call.
