In Israel, holy places, the World Center and a sea of brimstone await Ukrainian tourists
The Promised Land was filled with Bible truth, modern comfort, and wildlife.
Argoumenty i Fakty has listed five main reasons why you should visit Israel.
Go to the holy places to worship
Go to the Jordan River where Jesus was baptized.
It is said that anyone entering these "baptism grounds" will be affected by divine grace.
But Galilee was the land of Jesus' miracles - where water was turned into wine, where Jesus walked on water, calmed the storm, and where he performed miraculous fisheries.
It was there that Jesus appeared to his disciples after his resurrection.
But where you'll find the most holy places is in Jerusalem.
The believers walk through it on the Street of Suffering or the Way of the Cross (Latin: Via Dolorosa).
The road begins near the Antonia fortress (prince's palace), where the trial was held, then leads through the streets of the old city to the Church of the Holy Sepulchre on Golgotha, to the place of the Crucifixion, then to the place of the Anointing Stone and burial.
It is the center of the Christian world, a symbol of humanity's salvation.
According to Christian legend, the Monastery of the Cross is built on the spot where the tree used to make the cross on which Jesus was crucified grew.
Jerusalem is also home to the Jewish holiest place, the Wall of Mourning, which is the remnant of a temple destroyed by the Romans in 70 B.C.E.
Tradition has it that people of different faiths leave little words and prayers in the Bible and are then answered.
Traveling in heights
Visit the ruins of the fortress Massada, a former refuge from enemies built by Herod the Great in 25 B.C.E. for his family.
These ruins are located on the steep rocks of a mountain 450 m above sea level.
Only mountaineers can get there on their own.
For others, a cable car takes them to this historic summit.
In the north of the country, at an altitude of between 1,600 and 2,040 m, is the ski resort of Mount Hermont, which welcomes many tourists in the winter.
A shuttle can take you there from the foot of the mountain.
The total length of the ski slopes is 45 km.
Old beliefs say that pagan gods once lived on the top of the mountain.
Visiting unique museums
This country is home to nearly 300 museums.
It's impossible to visit them all in one stay.
Here are the five most interesting ones that are really worth a visit.
First, the Israel Museum, located near the Knesset (parliament).
It is home to the very old Qumran, or Dead Sea Scrolls, found in the caves of the Judean Desert, as well as nearly 500 miles of archaeological and anthropological artifacts.
