In Acre, the Hammam Al-Basha awaits you with its Turkish baths composed of moulds from visitors and watchers of the time.
Once in Caesarea, enter the only private Ralli Museum where you can admire Rodin's sculptures.
There are no guides or souvenir shops.
Admission is free and donations are prohibited.
The fifth museum is the Holocaust Museum, or Yad Vashem Memorial, in Tel Aviv, which is one of the most dramatic historical pages in history.
The most tragic part is the Children's Memorial, built in memory of the 1.5 million children who were murdered in concentration camps and gas chambers.
You go in there and you go into a total darkness.
The stars are shining.
You heard the names of the Jewish children and the names of the countries where they died.
Ukraine is also mentioned.
Health and wellbeing
Israel's three major seaports are located on the shores of the Mediterranean Sea, the Red Sea, and the Dead Sea.
Each has swimming pools, water parks, dolphinariums, and giant aquariums.
Note that you can swim in the Red Sea even in winter, as the water temperature does not drop below 21°C while the air temperature can reach 23°C.
The Dead Sea is even warmer and you can swim there all year long.
It is the world's most unique sea, and it is the lowest point on Earth, at 417 meters below sea level.
